This paper is primarily focused on developing a new hierarchical reinforcement learning (HRL) algorithm that is both general and efficient. The paper proposes a new scheme for HRL that uses off-policy experience for both higher and lower-level training, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also applies the proposed algorithm to robotic control tasks, which falls under the categories of robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper includes experiments with simulated robots, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) if the robots are using visual input. Overall, the paper's focus on developing a new HRL algorithm and applying it to robotic control tasks suggests that the most likely categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, and cs.CV, in that order.
